Record.CAVI-Lemma: Fr. of large RF panel amphora. From the province of Syracuse, acquired 1963. Contemporary with the Nikoxenos Painter; Coarse style. Last quarter sixth. Late sixth (Ashmead?Phillips).
Record.CAVI-Subject: A: Beazley in CB: Ajax and Achilles playing a board game, with Athena watching: at the upper left, part of her sleeve; part of her spear; at right, beard and shouldered spears of Ajax, with his raised hand making the sign for three.
Record.CAVI-Inscriptions: A: to left of the hand, facing Ajax: Αιας, retr.
Record.CAVI-Comments: From the body. Beazley interpreted the scene after London E 160, by the Nikoxenos Painter, ARV[2] 222/19, BSA 19, pls. 17,2, 19, and p. 234.
Record.AVI-Bibliography: CB (1931?63), iii, 3 n. 1. ? A. Ashmead and K. Phillips, Jr., CVA Bryn Mawr 1, USA 13 (1971), pl. 30,2.
